      Purchase options and add-ons

      • Bright and Playful Designs: Our toddler backpacks are available in a wide range of vibrant colors and playful patterns, perfect for kids of 2-5 and genders. They’re sure to spark joy and enthusiasm every time your child uses them.
      • Safety and Utility Features: Designed with a discreet reflective strip on the front pocket zipper for nighttime safety, our backpacks also include two handy D-rings on the front, ideal for attaching items like a child’s leash or a pencil case.
      • Eco-Friendly and Durable Construction: Crafted from resilient, eco-conscious materials, our backpacks are built to endure everyday use, ensuring they remain a trusted companion for your child over time.
      • Lightweight and Ergonomic Design: Engineered to be lightweight and comfortable, our backpacks minimize strain on your child’s back, making them easy and comfortable to carry throughout the day.
      • Reliable and Soft Components: Featuring sturdy zippers and soft, hand-sewn straps, our backpacks are designed to be gentle on your child’s skin while providing reliable functionality even with prolonged use.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Amazon Customer
      5 out of 5 stars
      Cute and functional
      This backpack is awesome! I use it for my 3 year olds daycare bag. It holds 3 changes of clothes, a sweatshirt, her bentgo lunchbox, and whatever toy or craft she brings in that day. It has two side pockets that would hold a toddler water bottle (think kids owala size). The pattern is really cute and girly, but dark enough that it won’t show stains. Speaking of stains, daycare doesn’t always fully close the lunch box so the inside of this bag has seen cherry juice, yogurt, apple sauce, ranch. Not a stain to be seen. It is still big for my toddler to carry by herself, but I usually carry the bag anyway. It’s really good quality and function for the price. Def recommend for those early years of daycare and pre-k!
